  "description": [
    "Jesse Jones Says RFC Earned 20 Million on LoansloB0 in 30s Reconstruction Finance Corp loans to the Baltimore Ohio Railroad were defended by Jesst Jones former RFC chairman ir a statement studied today by the Senate Banking Committee Mr Jones informed the com mittee that RFC has made a profit of more than 20 million from interest payments on its loans totalting 84 million in the 1930s He took issue with criticism by Senator Tobey Republican ol New Hampshire concerning the manner in which the loans were handled and the company al lowed to reorganize H also de nied that the railroads hiring ol former RFC employes had the slightest influence on any of our actions with respect to B Se O loans Probe Reopened by RFC Senator Tobey has not com mented on the Jonv statement but his oflice reported he might have something to say later RFC itself recently reopened an investigation of the B O loans Administrator W Stuart Syming ton explained that he had no wish to prejudge the matter but simply wanted to obtain all the facts The Senate committee on June 1 made public a report in which Senator Tobey almost four years ago"
